# Paws & Glow — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router (no `pages/` directory)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 (no `@apply` abuse — prefer utility classes)
- shadcn/ui components from /components/ui
- Supabase for DB, Auth, Storage
- React Three Fiber for 3D scenes
- GSAP for animations (use ScrollTrigger plugin)
- Zod for ALL validation schemas
- React Hook Form + @hookform/resolvers/zod

## Project Structure Rules
- Route groups: (public), (auth), (admin)
- 3D components live in /components/3d — always lazy load with next/dynamic + ssr:false
- Forms live in /components/forms
- Server Actions in /app/actions/
- Supabase client helpers in /lib/supabase/
- AI logic in /lib/ai/
- Types in /types/

## Coding Standards
- All Server Actions must be in files with "use server" at the top
- All Client Components must have "use client" at the top
- Always use TypeScript — no `any`, use `unknown` if uncertain
- Zod schemas co-located with their forms or in /lib/schemas/
- Environment variables: always use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for client-side vars
- Error handling: use try/catch in Server Actions, return typed results {data, error}
- Use `cn()` from /lib/utils for className merging
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Color palette: Indigo (primary), Slate (neutral), White (background)

## Database Rules
- Always use RLS in Supabase
- Use snake_case for SQL identifiers
- Prefer UUID primary keys
- All tables need created_at and updated_at timestamps

## AI Integration Rules
- GPT-4o Vision calls must be in Server Actions only (never expose API keys client-side)
- Always validate AI responses before returning to client
- DALL-E 3 image generation returns URLs — store in Supabase Storage, not raw OpenAI URLs

## Performance Rules
- 3D scenes must be lazy loaded (ssr:false)
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Prefetch critical routes
- Use React Suspense boundaries around async components
